sAuthor: Fakhree, M. A. A.[Mohammad A. A.]
Citation.sTitle: Solubility of Lamotrigine, Diazepam, and Clonazepam in Ethanol + Water Mixtures at 298.15 K
Citation.sAbstract: Experimental solubilities of three antiepileptic drugs, that is, lamotrigine, diazepam, and clonazepam in  ethanol + water mixtures at 298.15 K were reported. The solubility of drugs was increased with the addition  of ethanol, reached the maximum values, and then decreased with further increase in ethanol concentrations.  The Jouyban-Acree model was fitted to the data, and the solubilities were reproduced using two previously  developed relationships employing a number of the solvent s and solute s parameters and the solubility  data in monosolvents in which the overall mean deviations (OMDs) of the models were 6.2 %, 22.3 %, and  23.2 %.
